2016-06-22 14:29:32 Tumwesigye: You are required to provide the following documents
2016-06-22 14:30:31 Tumwesigye: 1. Disengagement letter OR Termination OR End of Contract letter of previous employer

4. Salary Bank statement for the last 3months

Visitor.Name: Patrick J
Chat.content:
2016-06-21 16:33:54 Patrick J: I need a clearance certificate for my company. How much is the payment and can i get it online after paying?
2016-06-22 09:59:01 System assistant: Tumwesigye has accepted the chat!
2016-06-22 09:59:01 Tumwesigye: Welcome to NSSF live chat, hold on while we attend to your query.
2016-06-22 12:55:57 Tumwesigye: Please carefully note the following requirements which MUST be attached along with the clearance application form.
 
For the Non-Members (Non registered and below threshold employers),
         Copy of the payment receipt of 250,000shs.
         Inspection letter from the Relationship Manager or the Auditor explaining that the employer is ineligible/below threshold.
         Six months payrolls and PAYEE schedules in soft copy (excel or scanned copies).
 
For the Non-Members who are willing to register,
         Copy of the payment receipt of 50,000shs.
         Copy of the NSSF employer registration form showing the employer has registered.
.
For registered employers who have not been audited in the last 24 months,
         Copy of the payment receipt of 50,000shs.
         Six months payrolls and PAYEE schedules in soft Copy (excel or scanned Copies).
         Six months SAT (self-assessment) by the employer.
 
For registered employers who have been audited in the last 24 months,
         Six months SAT (self-assessment) by the employer.
         Six months payrolls and PAYEE schedules in soft Copy (excel or scanned Copies).
 
 
Also Note
         You can now download the application form off the NSSF website using the link below, fill it in and thereafter submit it to the nearest branch.
Link to the clearance application form
https://www.nssfug.org/219/Forms
 
         You can also download the SAT off the NSSF website using the link below, do the assessment  and thereafter send it directly to mlubega@nssfug.org
Link to the SAT
https://www.nssfug.org/216/SelfAssessmentTemplate

2016-06-22 10:04:51 Tumwesigye: These a the specific requirements that you are required to provide
1. Disengagement letter OR Termination OR End of Contract letter of previous employer
2. Certified copy of appointment letter AND posting instructions
3. Certified copy of current pay slip ? For any of the last 3months worked under Exempted Employment
4. Salary Bank statement for the last 3months
5. Current Employer Identity Card
6. Validation Card
7. Current passport size photograph.
8. Personal Identification e.g. photocopy of Identity Card, Voters Card, Driving Permit, Passport, Financial Card, National Identity Card
9. Proof of Bank Account details e.g. Bank slip, Bank Statement

1-	2 Current passport size photographs.
2-	Certified copy of Letters of Administration or Probate 
3-	 Petition for letters of Administration or Grant of probate.
4-	 Death Certificate confirming demise of the member.
5-	 Introduction letter from the employer of the deceased member
6-	Copy of the work permit of the deceased member.
7-	 Bank statement where beneficiary would like to be paid in
8-	Passport ID of the claimant

2016-06-17 16:02:27 Tumwesigye: You are eligible to claim at the age of 50,once you are out of employment. We advise that you go to your nearest NSSF branch with the following requirements;
1. Current passport size photograph.
2. Personal Identification e.g. photocopy of Identity Card, Voters Card, Driving Permit, Passport, Financial Card, National Identity Card
3. Proof of Bank Account details e.g. Bank slip, Bank Statement
4. Present original documents when submitting claim for comparison with copies.
5. Disengagement letter OR Termination OR End of Contract letter OR Introduction letter from Employer

Visitor.Name: prasad

2016-06-17 14:11:46 System assistant: Tumwesigye has accepted the chat!
2016-06-17 14:11:46 Tumwesigye: Welcome to NSSF live chat, hold on while we attend to your query.
2016-06-17 14:17:26 Tumwesigye: Here are the details you have to provide when submitting your claim;
1. Disengagement letter OR Termination OR End of Contract letter
2. Evidence of Exit from Uganda e.g. Exit stamp from Uganda and/or Entry stamp to destination country.
3. Cancelled OR Expired work permit OR clearance from Immigration Department in case of absence of work permit
4. Current passport size photograph.
5. Personal Identification e.g. photocopy of Identity Card, Voters Card, Driving Permit, Passport, Financial Card, National Identity Card
6. Proof of Bank Account details e.g. Bank slip, Bank Statement
7. Present original documents when submitting claim for comparison with copies.

2016-06-17 11:56:47 Tumwesigye: Welcome to NSSF live chat, hold on while we attend to your query.
2016-06-17 11:57:56 Tumwesigye: Thank you for contacting us. In regard to the inquiry about your member update, to add a spouse, you will need to present a copy of your marriage certificate; to add a child; you will need to present a copy of his/her birth certificate to any of our nearest NSSF branch for the update.
2016-06-17 11:58:46 Tumwesigye: And then about withdrawal of benefits,
The NSSF Act administers and pays qualified contributing persons the following benefits as a matter of right;
1.     Age Benefit: This is paid to members who have reached the retirement age of 55. Age benefit can also be claimed on attaining the age of 50, provided the claimant has retired from employment
2.     Survivors Benefit: This is paid to the immediate surviving family (spouse and children) of the deceased member. In case the member did not have a spouse or children, the benefit is paid to parents if they solely depended upon the deceased member.
3.     Exempted Employment: This is paid to members who join excepted employment categories that have their own Social Protection Schemes e.g. public service, Army, Police etc
4.     Emigration Grant: This is paid to foreign or Ugandan members who are leaving the country permanently
5.     Invalidity Benefit: This is paid to members who can no longer be gainfully employed because of physical or mental incapacitation.
6.     Withdrawal Benefit: This is paid to a member if he or she attains the age of fifty years; and if he or she has not been employed under a contract of service for a period of one year immediately preceding his or her claim.

Visitor.Name: Craig Kinnear
Chat.content:
2016-06-16 15:10:45 Craig Kinnear: Withdrawing of funds
2016-06-16 15:19:31 System assistant: Tumwesigye has accepted the chat!
2016-06-16 15:19:31 Tumwesigye: Welcome to NSSF live chat, hold on while we attend to your query.
2016-06-16 15:20:07 Tumwesigye: Dear Craig
As per the Act, below are the five Products that NSSF administers and pays qualified contributing persons the following benefits as a matter of right
1. Age Benefit: This is paid to members who have reached the retirement age of 55. Age benefit can also be claimed on attaining the age of 50, provided the claimant has retired from employment
2. Survivors Benefit: This is paid to the immediate surviving family (spouse and children) of the deceased member. In case the member did not have a spouse or children, the benefit is paid to parents if they solely depended upon the deceased member.
3. Exempted Employment: This is paid to members who join excepted employment categories that have their own Social Protection Schemes e.g. public service, Army, Police etc
4. Emigration Grant: This is paid to foreign or Ugandan members who are leaving the country permanently
5. Invalidity Benefit: This is paid to members who can no longer be gainfully employed because of physical or mental incapacitation.
6. Withdrawal Benefit: This is paid to a member if he or she attains the age of fifty years; and if he or she has not been employed under a contract of service for a period of one year immediately preceding his or her claim
2016-06-16 15:26:10 Craig Kinnear: Hi Tumwesigye
2016-06-16 15:26:40 Craig Kinnear: Thank you for this. I emigrated in March 2015
2016-06-16 15:29:37 Craig Kinnear: I seem to have lost our chat
2016-06-16 15:32:04 Tumwesigye: Alright Craig
2016-06-16 15:32:15 Tumwesigye: This is what you have to provide
2016-06-16 15:33:51 Tumwesigye: 1. Disengagement letter OR Termination OR End of Contract letter
2. Evidence of permanent residence status or citizenship e.g. Passport or National ID, Green Card for US immigrants, Indefinite leave to Stay
Status for UK, Permanent residence card, settlement cards
3. Evidence of Exit from Uganda e.g. Exit stamp from Uganda and/or Entry stamp to destination country.
5.  work permits for all the work period jan13-mar15
Current passport size photograph.
6. Personal Identification e.g. photocopy of Identity Card, Voters Card, Driving Permit, Passport, Financial Card, National Identity Card
7. Proof of Bank Account details e.g. Bank slip, Bank Statement
2016-06-16 15:40:23 Craig Kinnear: H. Am I still connected?
2016-06-16 15:42:54 Tumwesigye: Yes

Visitor.Name: Sunita
Chat.content:
2016-06-16 11:49:00 Sunita: I would like to have information on survivors' benefit
2016-06-16 11:50:12 Sunita: Hello
2016-06-16 11:50:20 Sunita: One of our staff passed away last month
2016-06-16 11:50:35 Sunita: n we would like his registered dependent to get the money for NSSF
2016-06-16 11:51:04 Sunita: one of the requirements is Certified copies of petition to the letters of Administration and the Letters of Administration OR certified copies of the Will of Deceased
and Grant of probate.
2016-06-16 11:51:13 Sunita: what if this is not available
2016-06-16 11:51:15 System assistant: Tumwesigye has accepted the chat!
2016-06-16 11:51:15 Tumwesigye: Welcome to NSSF live chat, hold on while we attend to your query.
2016-06-16 11:52:02 Tumwesigye: Dear Sunita,
2016-06-16 11:52:20 Sunita: thanks
2016-06-16 11:52:21 Sunita: yes pls
2016-06-16 11:52:51 Tumwesigye: Remember to access proceeds from the estates of a deceased, it is important to get letters of Administration
2016-06-16 11:53:39 Tumwesigye: The letters contain all dependants left and an admin to stick a claim to the NSSF savings
2016-06-16 11:53:39 Sunita: letter of administration from who?
2016-06-16 11:53:58 Tumwesigye: From the court
2016-06-16 11:54:20 Tumwesigye: You could get a lawyer to help
2016-06-16 11:54:26 Sunita: they have a death certificate
2016-06-16 11:55:10 Sunita: ok thanks tumwesigye
2016-06-16 11:55:43 Sunita: but will provide the information to the spouse
2016-06-16 11:55:51 Tumwesigye: The death certificate only confirms death
2016-06-16 11:55:55 Sunita: is it easily possible to get this admin certificate
2016-06-16 11:56:48 Tumwesigye: Am sorry but i do not understand that question
2016-06-16 11:57:30 Sunita: i mean will the family have easy access to the certificate that is required from the lawyer or is it a hassle. u know in this difficult moment we would like the family to have less struggle as they are already struggling
2016-06-16 11:57:56 Tumwesigye: but maybe,.. Here are the details required
1. Certified copies of petition to the letters of Administration and the Letters of Administration OR certified copies of the Will of Deceased
and Grant of probate.
2. Death Certificate of the member.
3. Introduction letter from the employer of the deceased member OR Introduction letter from the LC.
4. For claimants not provided (registered/updated) by deceased member OR for new re-registrations - Baptism Certificates for Children
and Marriage Certificate for Spouse.
5. Current passport size photograph.
6. Personal Identification e.g. photocopy of Identity Card, Voters Card, Driving Permit, Passport, Financial Card, National Identity Card
7. Proof of Bank Account details e.g. Bank slip, Bank Statement
8. Present original documents when submitting claim for comparison with copies.
Specific Requirements
9. Map showing the burial ground details
2016-06-16 11:57:58 Sunita: i mean the letter of administration
2016-06-16 11:58:37 Sunita: thanks a lot

Visitor.Name: Ayo Jasper

2016-06-16 09:30:33 Ayo Jasper: When i am making a claim, what documents are required by the claimant provided by the government?
2016-06-16 09:40:25 Ayo Jasper: I also would like to confirm my details. Can it be provided online or the nearest branch?
2016-06-16 11:06:26 System assistant: Samali Nalwoga has accepted the chat!
2016-06-16 11:06:26 Samali Nalwoga: Welcome to NSSF live chat, hold on while we attend to your query.
2016-06-16 11:07:58 Samali Nalwoga: Below are the requirements;
1- Current passport size photograph.
2- Personal Identification e.g. photocopy of Identity Card, Voters Card, Driving Permit, Passport
3- Photocopy of NSSF Card
4- Proof of Bank Account details e.g. Bank slip
5- Disengagement letter or Termination or end of contract letter
6- Certified copy of appointment letter and posting instructions
7- Certified copy of current pay slip-For any of the 3months worked under Exempted Employment
8- Salary Bank statement for the last 3 months
9- Current employer Identity Card
10- Warrant card for Police Officers, Movement order for the Army.
7- Introduction Letter from Parliamentary Commission for Parliament Staff.

2016-06-10 11:33:12 System assistant: Diana Akurut has accepted the chat!
2016-06-10 11:33:12 Diana Akurut: Welcome to NSSF live chat, hold on while we attend to your query.
2016-06-10 11:33:32 Diana Akurut: hello Sravan, are you leaving the country

2016-06-10 11:34:29 sravan: Can you please help
2016-06-10 11:41:55 Diana Akurut: 1.2 Current passport size photographs
2. Personal Identification e.g. photocopy of Identity Card, Voters Card, Driving Permit, Passport, Financial Card, National Identity Card
3. Proof of Bank Account details e.g. Bank slip, Bank Statement
4. Disengagement letter OR Termination OR End of Contract letter
5. Evidence of Exit from Uganda e.g. Exit stamp from Uganda and/or Entry stamp to destination country.
6. Cancelled OR Expired work permit OR clearance from Immigration Department in case of absence of work permit
2016-06-10 11:42:04 Diana Akurut: those are the requirments needed
2016-06-10 11:43:02 Diana Akurut: it takes 21 working days to process the money if all the requirements have been submitted

2016-06-10 08:50:30 Diana Akurut: the whole proces takes 21 working Days
2016-06-10 08:51:57 Diana Akurut: the requirements needed are;
1. 2 Current passport size photographs
2. Personal Identification e.g. photocopy of Identity Card, Voters Card, Driving Permit, Passport, Financial Card, National Identity Card

2016-06-10 08:52:11 Diana Akurut: 4.Disengagement letter OR Termination OR End of Contract letter

Visitor.Name: Emily
Chat.content:
2016-06-07 15:04:55 Emily: Hello,
Please give me an overview of nssf ug?
2016-06-07 15:37:17 System assistant: Diana Akurut has accepted the chat!
2016-06-07 15:37:17 Diana Akurut: Welcome to NSSF live chat, hold on while we attend to your query.
2016-06-07 15:43:52 Diana Akurut: The National Social Security Fund (NSSF) is National Saving Scheme mandated by Government through the National Social Security Fund Act, Cap 222 (Laws of Uganda) to provide social security services to employees in Uganda.
It was established by an Act of Parliament (1985) to provide for its membership, payment of contributions to, and payment of benefits out of the Fund.
NSSF is a provident fund (pays out contributions in lump sum). It covers all employees in the private sector including Non Governmental Organizations, that are not covered by the Government's pension scheme. It is a scheme instituted for the protection of employees against the uncertainties of social and economic life.
 
The NSSF Vision
To be the Social Security Provider of choice
 
The NSSF Mission
To secure a better life for our growing membership by providing quality products, great customer service and offering competitive returns in a transparent and efficient environment
 
The NSSF Values
         Customer Centric
         Innovation
         Integrity
         Team Work
         Efficiency
 NSSF Benefits 
As per the Act, NSSF administers and pays qualified contributing persons the following benefits as a matter of right
Age Benefit
This is paid to members who have reached the retirement age of 55. Age benefit can also be claimed on attaining the age of 50, provided the claimant has retired from employment
Survivors Benefit
This is paid to the immediate surviving family (spouse and children) of the deceased member. In case the member did not have a spouse or children, the benefit is paid to parents if they solely depended upon the deceased member.
Exempted Employment
This is paid to members who join excepted employment categories that have their own Social Protection Schemes e.g. public service, Army, Police etc
Emigration Grant
This is paid to foreign or Ugandan members who are leaving the country permanently
Invalidity Benefit
This is paid to members who can no longer be gainfully employed because of physical or mental incapacitation.
   6.      Withdrawal Benefit
This is paid to a member if he or she attains the age of fifty years; and if he or she has not been employed under a contract of service for a period of one year immediately preceding his or her claim
Investments
The NSSF Board of Directors, through Management has a legal and fiduciary obligation to act in the best financial interest of the Fund's beneficiaries and to exercise the highest standard of care. Premised on the above, the Fund has established Investment Policy Guidelines and Strategies that are vital to all the Fund's stakeholders.
NSSF believes that the projected pension benefits can best be met by having the proper long term asset mix, including proper diversification as well as prudent management of risks.
The Board of Directors has approved an asset mix that has strong equity skew and considers the alternative asset class of Real Estate. This should enable the fund to achieve revenue targets that can sustain the desired interest levels to members.
NSSF has an array of permissible investments covering almost all sectors of the economy. These include; real estate development, energy, water, education, health, mortgage finance (both primary and secondary) and SME developments.
 
 Future Plans
Introduce a Client Self Service system
Introduce new social security products
Health Insurance
Unemployment
Education
HIV/AIDS
Maternity

2016-06-02 12:16:39 Diana Akurut: how may i help
2016-06-02 12:16:58 okeny caroline: how and when can i get my savings?
2016-06-02 12:18:22 okeny caroline: in case my employer miss out some months, who should i follow up to have the money deposited?
2016-06-02 12:20:33 okeny caroline: what are the requirements needed for me to withdraw my money when the time ripes?
2016-06-02 12:23:28 Diana Akurut: General Requirements
1. Current passport size photograph.
2. Personal Identification e.g. photocopy of Identity Card, Voters Card, Driving Permit, Passport, Financial Card, National Identity Card
3. Proof of Bank Account details e.g. Bank slip, Bank Statement
4. Present original documents when submitting claim for comparison with copies.
Specific Requirements
Age Benefit at 55 years
1. Introduction letter from the Employer OR Local Council OR National Identity Card
2. Work permit for Non Ugandans
Withdraw benefit at 50 years
1. Disengagement letter OR Termination OR End of Contract letter OR Introduction letter from Employer
2. Work permit for Non Ugandans
Withdrawal Benefit (following exempted employment)
1. Disengagement letter OR Termination OR End of Contract letter of previous employer
2. Certified copy of appointment letter AND posting instructions
3. Certified copy of current pay slip ? For any of the last 3months worked under Exempted Employment
4. Salary Bank statement for the last 3months
5. Current Employer Identity Card
6. Warrant card for police officers and Movement order for the Army.
7. Introduction Letter from the Parliamentary Commission for Parliament Staff.
Emigration Grant
1. Disengagement letter OR Termination OR End of Contract letter
2. Introductory letter from the Embassy ? Ugandans permanently relocating
3. Evidence of permanent residence status or citizenship e.g. Passport or National ID, Green Card for US immigrants, Indefinite leave to Stay
Status for UK, Permanent residence card, settlement cards
4. Evidence of Exit from Uganda e.g. Exit stamp from Uganda and/or Entry stamp to destination country.
5. Cancelled OR Expired work permit OR clearance from Immigration Department in case of absence of work permit
6. Refugees: Introduction letter from Office of the Prime Minister AND/OR Repatriation card from UNHCR OR Letter from International
Organisation for Migration.
7. Marriage certificate and spouse visa or dependant?s pass where applicable.
Invalidity Benefit
1. Disengagement letter OR Termination OR End of Contract letter OR Introduction letter from the last Employer or Local Council
2. Clinical notes or documents indicating history of illness (The client may be required to see the Fund Doctor)
3. Certified High court order appointing Manager for Estate of Persons of Unsound mind
Survivors Benefit
1. Certified copies of petition to the letters of Administration and the Letters of Administration OR certified copies of the Will of Deceased
and Grant of probate.
2. Death Certificate of the member.
3. Introduction letter from the employer of the deceased member OR Introduction letter from the LC.
4. For claimants not provided (registered/updated) by deceased member OR for new re-registrations - Baptism Certificates for Children
and Marriage Certificate for Spouse
2016-06-02 12:24:05 Diana Akurut: those are the requirements for the different types
